### Cause of the Issue
In [cli.py](file:///home/forcewake/coding-agent-battles-init/runs/2026-06-22-bb-001-broken-cli-argument-telemetry-rerun/agents/agy/workspace/bb001_wordfreq/cli.py#L24-L30), the parser option `--min-length` was configured with `action="store_true"`, meaning it did not accept any argument values and only registered as a boolean flag. When running the CLI with `--min-length 4` (e.g. in the unit tests), the argument parser interpreted `4` as the positional argument (`path`) and the actual file path as an unrecognized argument, leading to an error.

### Solution
1. Updated [cli.py](file:///home/forcewake/coding-agent-battles-init/runs/2026-06-22-bb-001-broken-cli-argument-telemetry-rerun/agents/agy/workspace/bb001_wordfreq/cli.py) to replace `action="store_true"` with `type=int` for the `--min-length` argument.
2. Verified the fix by running `pytest`, confirming that the test suite now passes successfully.
